E-LIFE-FINANCIAL-SERVICES.name: E-Life Financial Services (Yisheng Jinfu)
E-LIFE-FINANCIAL-SERVICES.tagline: HNA Group's integrated travel fintech platform providing foreign exchange, payments, and consumer lending services to Chinese travelers
E-LIFE-FINANCIAL-SERVICES.overview: E-Life Financial Services (Yisheng Jinfu / 易生金服) is a travel-focused fintech platform under HNA Group, one of China's largest conglomerates and parent of Hainan Airlines. Founded in 2016, E-Life provides comprehensive financial services for travelers including foreign exchange, traveler's cheques, tax refund services, and consumer loans. The company operates as part of HNA Capital, leveraging the group's extensive travel and aviation network to offer integrated financial solutions. E-Life serves millions of Chinese outbound travelers with a suite of services designed to streamline cross-border financial needs.

EARNIX.name: Earnix
EARNIX.tagline: AI-powered dynamic pricing and decisioning platform for insurance and banking organizations with real-time personalization
EARNIX.overview: Earnix is a leading AI-powered pricing and decisioning platform for insurance and banking organizations, founded in 2001 by Sammy Krikler and Yoni Cheifetz in Israel. The cloud-based platform combines artificial intelligence with advanced analytics to enable real-time modeling, simulations, and personalized price and product offerings. Earnix achieved unicorn status in 2021 after raising $75 million at a $1 billion valuation. The company serves major insurance carriers and retail banks globally, helping them optimize pricing strategies while maintaining regulatory compliance. In 2025, Earnix acquired Zelros to expand its AI capabilities in the insurance space.

EAT-JUST.name: Eat Just
EAT-JUST.tagline: Pioneer in plant-based and cultivated meat producing JUST Egg and GOOD Meat with first FDA/USDA approval for cultured chicken
EAT-JUST.overview: Eat Just is a pioneering food technology company producing both plant-based foods and cultivated meat. The company became a unicorn in 2016 and has been making moves toward an IPO with a target valuation of $3 billion. Through its GOOD Meat subsidiary, Eat Just became one of the first companies to receive both FDA and USDA approval for cultivated chicken in 2023. GOOD Meat has raised $267 million, making it the most funded cell-cultured meat company to date. The company's flagship products include JUST Egg plant-based egg substitute and GOOD Meat cultivated chicken, sold in Singapore and approved for sale in the United States.

EBANX.overview: EBANX is a leading payment platform connecting global companies with consumers in emerging markets across Latin America, Africa, and Asia. Founded in 2012 in Curitiba, Brazil by João Del Valle, Alphonse Voigt, and co-founders, EBANX became Brazil's first southern-region tech unicorn in 2019 after investment from FTV Capital. The company serves over 1,600 global digital businesses including Microsoft, Sony, TikTok, Coinbase, Uber, AliExpress, and Ubisoft, processing payments across e-commerce, gaming, SaaS, streaming, and travel verticals. EFISHERY.name: eFishery
EFISHERY.tagline: Indonesian aquaculture technology company that became first global unicorn in the sector, now under investigation following massive financial fraud revelations
EFISHERY.overview: eFishery was an Indonesian aquaculture technology company founded in 2013 that became the world's first unicorn in the aquaculture industry. In December 2024, an internal investigation revealed massive financial fraud: the company had allegedly inflated revenue from $157M to $752M in the first nine months of 2024. Co-founders Gibran Huzaifah and Chrisna Aditya were suspended and later arrested. FTI Consulting now manages the company and has concluded eFishery is not commercially viable, recommending wind-down. Investors including SoftBank, Temasek, and Goldman Sachs face losses exceeding $300M.

EGYM.tagline: Global fitness technology unicorn making gyms work for everyone through connected equipment, personalized training, and corporate wellness solutions
EGYM.overview: EGYM is a Munich-based fitness technology company that provides connected fitness solutions for gym operators, corporate wellness programs, and healthcare providers. Founded by Philipp Roesch-Schlanderer after experiencing frustration with ineffective gym equipment, EGYM has grown to serve over 18,000 fitness and health centers globally with 6 million monthly active users. The company's platform combines smart gym equipment with personalized training software and the EGYM Wellpass corporate benefit program connecting 17,000 sports partners with 14,000 corporate customers representing over 3 million eligible employees.

EIGENLAYER.name: EigenLayer
EIGENLAYER.tagline: Ethereum restaking protocol enabling validators to secure multiple networks simultaneously with $18B+ TVL dominating 85% of restaking market
EIGENLAYER.overview: EigenLayer is the pioneering Ethereum restaking protocol that allows ETH validators to opt-in to securing additional networks and services while earning extra rewards. Founded by Sreeram Kannan, the protocol has grown from $1.1B to over $18B in total value locked throughout 2024, representing 85%+ of the overall restaking market. EigenLayer's innovation enables the creation of 'Actively Validated Services' (AVS) that can leverage Ethereum's security without bootstrapping their own validator set. The EIGEN token launched in October 2024 at approximately $6.7 billion fully diluted valuation.

ENPAL.tagline: Germany's leading greentech unicorn revolutionizing residential solar with integrated systems, heat pumps, and Europe's first solar securitization
ENPAL.overview: Enpal is Germany's leading greentech unicorn and top residential solar provider, offering an integrated one-stop-shop for solar panels, battery storage, heat pumps, EV chargers, and smart energy management. Founded in 2017 by Mario Kohle in Berlin, Enpal has digitized the adoption of green energy for homes with its no-down-payment rental model. The company has been profitable since 2022 and has surpassed €5 billion in total financing commitments, recently completing Europe's first public residential solar ABS at €240M and partnering with the European Investment Bank.

products.name: Solar & Battery System
products.description: Complete photovoltaic installation with integrated battery storage for energy independence and grid services

products.name: Heat Pump Solutions
products.description: Efficient heat pump systems integrated with solar for sustainable home heating and hot water

products.name: Smart Energy Manager
products.description: Intelligent platform managing distributed energy resources, optimizing consumption, and enabling grid participation

highlights.title: Surpassed €5 billion in total financing commitments
Completed Europe's first public residential solar ABS at €240M
Secured €1.1B refinancing from Barclays, BofA, Credit Agricole, CPP
EIB Group backed €100M in Europe's first public solar securitization
Integrated 250,000 distributed energy resources into Enpal system
Profitable since 2022 with leading German residential solar market position

ENTRATA.name: Entrata
ENTRATA.tagline: Leading multifamily property management software platform reaching $503M revenue with AI-powered autonomous property solutions
ENTRATA.overview: Entrata is a comprehensive property management software platform serving the multifamily housing industry. Founded in 2003 by Johnny Hanna in Lehi, Utah, the company provides an all-in-one platform for property accounting, marketing, leasing, facilities management, and resident services. Entrata has grown to serve over 20,000 customers and achieved $503M in revenue in 2024. The company received a $200M minority investment from Blackstone at a $4.3B valuation, with Silver Lake as a key investor through $707M in total funding.

products.name: Entrata Platform
products.description: Comprehensive property management suite including accounting, marketing, leasing, and maintenance for multifamily properties

products.name: ResidentPortal
products.description: Digital resident experience platform for online payments, maintenance requests, community engagement, and smart home integration

products.name: Entrata AI
products.description: AI-powered autonomous property management tools for automated communications, predictive analytics, and operational efficiency

highlights.title: Revenue reached $503M in October 2024 (up from $447M in 2023)
Blackstone invested $200M at $4.3B valuation
Acquired Colleen AI for enhanced automation capabilities
Expanded AI platform for autonomous property management
Serving 20,000+ property management customers across US
Total funding reached $707M with Silver Lake as key investor

EVENUP.name: EvenUp
EVENUP.tagline: AI-powered legal technology transforming personal injury law with intelligent case management
EVENUP.overview: EvenUp is a pioneering legal technology company founded in 2019 that leverages artificial intelligence to revolutionize personal injury law. The company's mission is to close the justice gap by empowering personal injury attorneys and their clients to achieve fairer outcomes faster. EvenUp's Claims Intelligence Platform, powered by its proprietary Piai AI model, is trained on hundreds of thousands of injury cases and millions of medical records. As of October 2025, EvenUp has achieved a valuation exceeding $2 billion and has helped resolve over 200,000 cases, securing more than $10 billion in damages for injury victims. The company serves over 2,000 law firms, including 20% of the top 100 US personal injury firms, with ARR doubling year-over-year.

products.description: EvenUp main product offering

New AI products account for 90% of new sales, driving rapid adoption.
